National Average Interest Rate
The National average is only 0.06%.
Online banks have a lower operating cost, larger area of influence, and can offer a more competitive interest rate. This rate is currently up to
21.7 times higher than the national average!


1.30% doesn't seem that high, is it worth it?
Absolutely! It may not seem that much, though with $2,000 in the bank for emergencies or other savings, you'll earn $26.00 a year. For a 15 minute investment, that's making the equivalent of
$104.00 an hour. Your money will now work for you forever. Invest more and the return just gets better.


Online Savings vs CD Account
High Yield Savings often pays equal to low-term CD (certificate of deposit) accounts. And, you have much more flexibility with your money. With a CD, you can't touch your money without penalty for the agreed term. That's not true with an online savings account.





